<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col"></div>
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-sm-10">

            <div class="card mt-4">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h1 class="h3">Hello {{name}}!</h1>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 text-center">About this session</h2>
                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush text-center">
                        <li class="list-group-item">There is a token present, saved as a cookie named <b>htaccess</b>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">The requested token is meant to be for the {{audBy}} role.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">It will expire at {{expire}} <br> ( set to be 5 minutes from the
                            moment
                            you requested it )</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">After it has expired, you will need to request a new one to access
                            this site.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="h4 mt-4">About the jwt</h2>
                    <p class="text-justify">
                        It allows stateless communication with the server while making sure the data sent back and
                        forth are valid. If a user wanted to change the integrity of the data saved within the token,
                        the server would throw an exception when trying to verify the token's signature. You can try
                        this out by opening the browser's developer tools and change a single part of the token. Upon
                        refreshing of this page, you will not be authenticated anymore.
                    </p>
                    <button id="home-delete-jwt-cookie" class="btn btn-outline-danger float-right mt-4">
                        <i class="fas fa-cookie-bite"></i>
                        Delete JWT cookie
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col"></div>
    </div>
